==English==
===Etymology===
From {{OE.}}; originated from [[Saxon]] language, with a similar name Alwyn or Alwin,  meaning "a noble friend" or "elf wine".
From Old High German [[adal]]- = 'noble' + -[[win]]- = 'friend'.

===Proper noun===
[[Category:English proper nouns]]
'''Alvin'''

#{{given name|male|}} A male [[given name]].

